==English==
===Etymology===
* [[swift]] + [[boat]]
* From the Swift Boat Veterans for Truth's attacks during the 2004 U.S. presidential campaign. [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swift_Boat_Veterans_for_Truth] {{rfv-sense}}

===Noun===
'''[[swift]] [[boat]]'''
# A small, [[shallow]] [[draft]] water vessel used by the United States [[Navy]] for counterinsurgency (COIN) operations during the Vietnam War; Fast Patrol Craft (PCF).

===Transitive Verb===
'''to swift boat''' (alternate spelling, '''swiftboat''') {{rfv-sense}}
# to put forth sensational lies about a political figure as part of a public relations campaign against him/her

